race.comment: HORIZONS (11) proved too slick for Attica two-back, then was a month between runs when a fading fifth over 1500m at Hawkesbury. Norton bit goes on and will take catching out to the 1800m. Value player. OCEANFRONT (3) the penny has finally dropped for this gelding, and he deserves his chance in town. Last two wins at Newcastle had a ton of merit and can push forward from the sticky draws. Top three prospect. HIGHBORN HARRY (8) has a sense of timing fourth up from the soft draw. Motored late from the wide gate when a closing third to OCEANFRONT over 1890m at Newcastle. Can go forward and prove hard to stop. NATOYA (4) racing well on the provincial tracks and will relish the heavy surface. Rounded them up effortlessly as fav when a dominant winner over 1600m at Newcastle. Each way player.
